?(future) can we set IPv4 in config prior to install?
copy 99force-ipv4 file to /etc/apt/apt.conf.d 

set keyboard to US...

sudo apt-get -o Acquire::ForceIPv4=true update
sudo apt-get -o Acquire::ForceIPv4=true dist-upgrade

sudo rpi-update  //update firmware

sudo apt-get -o Acquire::ForceIPv4=true install alsa-base alsa-utils
sudo apt-get -o Acquire::ForceIPv4=true install libasound2-dev
sudo apt-get autoremove

git clone https://github.com/sennt18/tjwave.git

sudo apt-get -o Acquire::ForceIPv4=true install npm

npm install node-gyp

npm install

instructions to get a new nodejs package
curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_7.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

npm install underscore
cd 


sudo apt-get install paprefs  //pulseaudio preferences....
** note user pi working for pulse audio / bluetooth, but not root.....
